e Points, skills and armor?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I haven't started playing yet. I'm on my way over from Asheron's Call. I've read the Prima Kunark Strategy Guide and the Everquest Manual. Both books state that you get practice points to train skills. Neither tells me how many you get and when. <br>
<br>
Specifically, can a wizard forge armor? Can a wizard wear plate? Can I save points and use them later? Do I need to save points to learn languages if I am a Ranger? What languages will I already know?<br>
<br>
Most of this information, you already know since you have been playing. But, you must have learned it somewhere. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Any help is going to be greatly appreciated. I will probably come to Vazaelle since it is a new server and I generally like playing with veterans that enjoy the game and are not so much into powerleveling.<br>
<br>
I'm looking at Erudite Wizard. Any other suggestions are appreciated. I don't need to level fast or easy.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umiriandartheranger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miriandar the Ranger</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>2/13/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:33:44 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Practice Points, skills and armor?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Forging armor: There are trade skills with in EQ for creating some items, specifically blacksmithing for creating some types of armor. Any race/class combination may improve their ability in trade skills.<br>
<br>
Wizard armor: Very minimal. Wizards in EQ may not wear plate, chain, or leather type armor. At early levels, you are limited to cloth and raw silk. As you progress, there are magical armor pieces wearable by Intelligence stat-based casters.<br>
<br>
Practice points: You gain 5 practice points per level and they may be saved for later use.<br>
<br>
Languages: This is an aspect of EQ that is not really used at all except by INT casters who (I think) need specific languages to advance their special ability to Research spells. Starting languages known will be based on the race of your character. All characters start knowing the &quot;Common&quot; language. For a ranger, there are three races, human, wood elf, and half-elf. Wood elves and half-elves start knowing &quot;Common&quot; and &quot;Elvish&quot;. I'm not sure about Human rangers, but they may only start knowing &quot;Common&quot;. Rangers do not need to know languages unless they wish to roleplay. Discussions in languages others do not understand are frowned upon by those that do not know what is being said. If two people wish to communicate privately, typically /tell is used instead of using a different language.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
